owAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Agro Healing</span><hr size=1> I was in CT the other day in the thron room.  Our tank pulls about 4 lizzies.  I am in the corner medding up.  The tank's health begins to drop, so I let off a greater heal when he is at 3 bubbles of health.  All the lizard, except for the one the tank is on, runs and beats on me.<br>
<br>
What I would like to know, is what strategies do the more experienced clerics have on agro healing?<br>
<br>
Should I have healed when the tank was at 3 bubbles or waited a bit more, then healed?  Would that have made  a difference?  I understand that when i let off the GHeal, it was if I was doing 300 dmg to all 4 lizards, thus agroing myself.<br>
<br>
Should I have let off a regualr heal first, to not agro the lizards as much, so the tank would have an easier time to taunt off me?<br>
<br>
When the mobs agro on me, should I fight back, or just wait for the tanks to taunt off me.<br>
<br>
Would another solution be to maybe root the other mobs first then cast heal?<br>
<br>
Just a few questions.  I'm sure that there are more floating around in my head.  I would appreciate any help on this matter.  Thank youvery much for your time.<br>
<br>
Angeyl<br>
Tier'Dal Priestess of Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucamdarlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CamdarLanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/4/00 11:00:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agro Healing</span><hr size=1> Ahh,<br>
<br>
Welcome to &quot;Why Clerics love Enchanters&quot; 101.<br>
<br>
It is an old axiom in most dungeons that you can't go in deep without a Cleric and a Cleric won't go in without and Enchanter.  Why?  Because the Cleric keeps the party alive and the Enchanter keeps the Cleric alive.<br>
<br>
You have just posted the exact reason why.  What needs to happen in this case is that if the Tank is going to pull mulitple mobs, the enchanter needs to Mez the other ones before you heal the tank.  Or, if the tank is falling real fast, he needs to mez the ones that are on you as fast as possible.<br>
<br>
What, there is no Enchanter you say?  This makes it much more difficult.  <br>
<br>
1.  Make sure the group has a second tank (With Taunt) assigned to do nothing more then pull mobs off you.  He/She is your guardian and MUST pull the mobs off you as soon as possible, then turn back to the main fight.  <br>
<br>
2. Keep both Divine Aura and Divine Barrier Mem'd at ALL times.  I am lvl 55 and have had both mem'd since lvl 29.  Hot Key your Divine Spells and do not be afraid to use them.  Use the Divine, then after mobs have left you alone, click on the flashing Icon and heal who you need to. <br>
<br>
3.  Make sure there is a back up healer (Shaman, Druid) assigned by the group leader to watch your hps.  This is especially important if there is no enchanter in your group.<br>
<br>
4.  If they are unable or unwilling to protect the person that is there to keep them alive, then I would consider finding a new group.  Yes, I know sometimes it takes a while to find one.  But in the long run, you will teach them how to treat a cleric and you will not spend an hour or so trying to get back to your corpse.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps some,<br>
<br>
I am,<br>
<br>
Camdar Sol'Dara<br>
55 Templar<br>
&quot;Circle of Truth&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udragon257.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dragon257</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/8/00 8:35:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agro Healing</span><hr size=1> Camdar hit it right on the head...<br>
<br>
In order for the Cleric to remain alive, there MUST be one of the following...<br>
<br>
1. A Taunt Heavy Group, a group with lots of Melee classes that can Taunt things off the Cleric will do fine with just one Cleric backing them up.<br>
<br>
2. A back-up healer. It's the back-up healers job to do little else than keep you alive if you get agro'd. But this can cause Monsters to run back and forth between healers.<br>
<br>
3. Bring an Enchanter along. Mezzed MoBs have no teeth, You can heal to your hearts content, worst thing that could happen is the one fighting creature could make a run at you. This, of course is based on the skill of the Enchanter.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, the flip side, here are some things you can do to improve your chances and fun when with different groups.<br>
<br>
1. Let the group know how you will be performing your role.<br>
<br>
2. Let certain key members in your group know what they need to do to help keep you, and thus the rest of the party, alive.<br>
<br>
3. Call Evac when needed (if available) or sound the retreat. You are the one that's best suited to know when it's time to get out (barring the presence of an Enchanter) If it's time to leave, use your Devine Barrier and run. Once again, you can get people to their corpses quickly. A Warrior can buy the party a lot more escape time than a Cleric can.<br>
<br>
If an Enchanter is present, they should be directing all aspects of combat. When there is no Enchanter, that task falls on the Cleric. Both these classes need to let their party know how their mana is doing, when it's good to pull, and when it's not good to pull.<br>
<br>
So it really becomes your job to be an expert combat strategist. Besides, most of the rest of your time is spent looking at a book anyway. So you have plenty of time to master combat strategy. <p><center><strong>
~Damahn Amungmehn</strong><br>
Cleric of the 30th Cross<br>
