Dragons Protectorate</a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarrach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arrach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/9/00 6:52:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agro Healing</span><hr size=1> Other spells to have handy for this situation are stun and root.  When there is no enchanter, when your enchanter is having a hard time, or when soloing, these two spells will help provide crowd control.  Root one beating on you, then move outside his melee range.  If you are having trouble getting root off, stun one first, then root.  Not as effective as having an enchanter or a taunter, but still a useful trick of the trade. <p>Arrach<br>
Servant of Innoruuk<br>
Soul Assassins</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubinoche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binoche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/14/00 11:26:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agro Healing</span><hr size=1> Other means by which you can asssit the tanks without aggro healing exist. They will reduce the rate of tanks HPs being dropped, and keep the rest of the mobs off you for a while.<br>
<br>
-- Assist the tank, chain stunning - if you have 4 mobs on the tank, now only 3 are beating on him. And if you have a tank targeting the toughest mob [ or the healing mob] (as he should)...your stuns are preventing the most damage at little mana cost, and you wont get aggroed.<br>
<br>
<br>
-- Finnish the target mob off with a nuke. 1 More not beating him up.<br>
<br>
-- root the greenies or low blues and ask the tanks to back away- the targeted mob will follow.<br>
<br>
-- Bob for mana all the time ) i cant tell you how many times i have ended a fight with just as much mana as when we started , just because i took the time to med betwqeen stuns / heals....<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/14/00 12:47:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro Healing</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
<br>
I agree with much that as said already so will not repeat it. One more issue, however, is where you decide to hunt. Some mobs don't take much notice of healers. Others are the opposite extreme, and aggro on healers the first chance they get. Most are somewhere in between. Experienced clerics learn the various mobs you can and can't get away with healing infront of.<br>
<br>
Take two extremes. Fighting Cyclops and Seafuries in OOT, I could CH a Warrior or Mage pet and then med at the mob's feet and it would ignore me once aggro'd on the tank. A cleric's dream. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If the mob aggroed on anyone, it was the chanter who was nuking cos he was bored LOL. The opposite extreme was ... you guessed it .. Cazic Thule. Those lizzies HATE HATE HATE clerics (or any healers), and you fly up to the top of their hate list as soon as you cast. I found this the absolute worst place in Norrath for this.<br>
<br>
There are various solutions to this. I died there too often around level 30, usually in pick-up groups but also in guild  groups as well, which wasn't much fun, so decided, that absence was the better part of prudence (hehe) and chose to hunt mostly in Paw instead up to 36 or so (far less crowded too at that time). Sure, gnolls are not keen on healers either, but it's easy compared to Cazic (and the people I met there were nice too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). Well that was my experience anyway.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
Felishanna Secretlight<br>
Cleric of Tunare of 56 Seasons<br>
Heroes of the Old Lands<br>
Lanys T'Vyl. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugtath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gtath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/15/00 12:26:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/images/broodwar/popup/corsair.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro Healing</span><hr size=1> Another subtle point is that if the tank you need to heal is a monk or SK, ask them to feign death before you heal them.  Mobs don't care if you heal a corpse.<br>
<br>
