<br>
Cleric of the 41st Prayer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udokuga.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dokuga</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/17/00 3:54:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/dokugatiyohali/licking_gecko.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro Healing</span><hr size=1> Actually Gtath, not exactly sure how this works but....<br>
I was in RM hunting HGs with some guildies the other night, stuff went bad, and I ended up feigned near the zone with a bub of HP left.  An ogre shammie came buy and cast regen on me to help me out.  much to the Shammie's dismay and my own, an enraged Hill Giant came along and started pounding on me again, despite the fact that I had been feigned for quite some time.  I refeigned and it reagroed on the Shaman.  /shrug. <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dokugatiyohali/dokuga_ban2.jpg" border="0" </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=worthy>Worthy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://facelink.com/edit/raw/image/98/2464498.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/17/00 7:32:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/edit/raw/image/98/2464498.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro Healing</span><hr size=1> Just one more note, when you Divine Aura, and call Evac, make sure you click it off before they leave, or, you will be all alone there. It happened to me once in Perma, playing with te gobbies. We got overwelmed. I did a AOE heal to pull argo on me(A useful tactic when used right, being we can take a few hits.), cuz I was full HP, and every one else was beat up, and, I wanted the druid clear to evac. I then did my DA. Smiling as the gobbies tried to beat me to no avail, while waiting to be teleported to safety. hehe...<br>
<br>
But then.....<br>
<br>
THe rest of my party got evaced, while my Divine Aura PROTECTED me from the evac effect.   YIKES! <br>
